A. If you already have a disk image (e.g., disk.img) and your script (data_carver.py)
	python data_carver.py disk.img


B. If you want to create a disk image and then carve it (Windows, using FTK Imager or Win32 Disk Imager for imaging, then Python for carving)
	
	python data_carver.py disk.img

C. If you want a one-liner for PhotoRec (cross-platform, recovers deleted files from a physical drive or image):
	
	photorec /log /d recovered_files

D. For Linux (create disk image and carve in one line):

	sudo dd if=/dev/sdX of=disk.img bs=4M && python data_carver.py disk.img

Summary Table
Task	One-liner
Carve disk image	python data_carver.py disk.img
Use PhotoRec	photorec /log /d recovered_files
(Linux) Image + carve	sudo dd if=/dev/sdX of=disk.img bs=4M && python data_carver.py disk.img
